  "texts": [
    "23We can deduce the OPE structure of these vertex operators with the free fields using the action of their modes on the ground states.",
    "For example,ξ ± (z)[|Φ w ⟩] σ w = r≤±w/2 [ξ ± r∓w/2 |Φ w ⟩] σ w z -r-1/2, (3.9) which implies that ξ ± (z) V w m 1,m 2 (x i; z i) = O (z -z i) ∓w-12.",
    "Similarly, one finds thatξ ± (z) V w A m 1,m 2 (x i; z i) = O (z -z i) ∓w-12for even w and A ∈ {±}.",
    "It was observed in [15] that the vertex operatorV w m 1,m 2 (0; z) = exp f w m 1,m 2 (z), (3.10)wheref w m 1,m 2 (z) = 2m 1 + w -1 2 ϕ 1 + 2m 1 iκ 1 + 2m 2 + w + 1 2 ϕ 2 + 2m 2 iκ 2,correctly reproduces this OPE structure with the symplectic bosons, where ϕ i and κ i are the bosonized fields given in (2.19).",
    "All that remains is to consider the OPE structure with the fermionic free fields F ±."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "It was observed in [15] that the vertex operatorV w m 1,m 2 (0; z) = exp f w m 1,m 2 (z), (3.10)wheref w m 1,m 2 (z) = 2m 1 + w -1 2 ϕ 1 + 2m 1 iκ 1 + 2m 2 + w + 1 2 ϕ 2 + 2m 2 iκ 2,correctly reproduces this OPE structure with the symplectic bosons, where ϕ i and κ i are the bosonized fields given in (2.19)."
